tuation you are in.\n\n- Giridhar Alwar, My Quest For Happy Life\n|\nNo matter how kind you are, always expect a few imbeciles.\n\n- Criss Jami, Healology\n|\nWe will remember the hurt, the injustice, and the trauma, but we can forgive the sinner.\n\n- Cathy Burnham Martin, The Bimbo Has Brains: And Other Freaky Facts\n|\nIn the story of life'Hope' is the Hero who protects the Lady Love 'Dream (Desire from the bad guy 'Fear'.\n\n- Wordions\n|\nFor any writer who wants to keep a journal, be alive to everything, not just to what you're feeling, but also to your pets, to flowers, to what you're reading.\n\n- May\n|\nYou see, I was ready to swim deep for youBut you felt like this was skin deep for youNo coffin, but I'd die for youNo coughing, but I'd lie for you\n\n- Bandile\n|\nIt is hard enough to remember my opinions, without also remembering my reasons for them!\n\n- Friedrich\n|\nTo be alive, it seemed to me, as I stood there in all kinds of sorrow, was to be both original and reflection, and to be dead was to be split off, to be reflection alone.\n\n- Teju Cole, Open City\n|\nLike all bitter men, Flint knew less than half the story and was more interested in unloading his own peppery feelings than in learning the truth.\n\n- John\n|\nThere is nothing better than love, kindness and forgiveness to create enduring peace.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nBeing alone can be good. It's easy to find peace alone. But sometimes, being alone is a king of death.\n\n- Dean Koontz, Chase\n|\nOur souls are but leaves in a storm, and only the gods know where we will come to rest.\n\n- David Gemmell, Lion of Macedon\n|\nIt's in my blood, as magic is in yours.' His mouth is still smiling, but his tone is somber. 'I couldn't stop writing even if I wanted to.\n\n- Elora Bishop, Braided: A Lesbian Rapunzel\n|\nI wish for you a goodnight of sleep, sweet dreams, and a smiling morning.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nSometimes, people don’t need our homes to live in or our bodies to lean on. All they need are our h